<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p class="updated">Last updated: March 18, 2026</p>

<p>game:out ("we", "our", or "us") is a mobile application for outdoor navigation events and activity tracking. This policy explains what data we collect, why we collect it, and how it is used.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

<h3>Location Data</h3>
<p>We collect precise GPS coordinates while you are actively recording an activity or participating in an event. This data is stored locally on your device and, at the end of an event, uploaded to our servers solely to calculate results and generate maps visible to you and event organisers. Location data is never sold or shared with advertisers.</p>

<h3>Account Information</h3>
<p>When you create an account we collect your email address and a display name (your "trail name"). This is managed through Firebase Authentication (Google).</p>

<h3>Activity and Event Data</h3>
<p>GPS tracks, elapsed time, elevation, and control-punch records for activities you record or events you participate in are stored in your account. You can delete your data at any time from the app settings.</p>

<h3>Payment Information</h3>
<p>If you pay an entry fee for a paid event, payment is processed by Stripe. We do not store your card number or payment details — these go directly to Stripe under their own <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy">privacy policy</a>.</p>

<h3>Bluetooth (BLE) — TrailPass</h3>
<p>With your permission, the app scans for Bluetooth Low Energy signals from nearby users who also have TrailPass enabled. Only an anonymised device identifier is recorded, along with the time and place of the encounter. This feature can be disabled at any time in Settings.</p>

<h3>NFC</h3>
<p>NFC is used only to read event control checkpoints placed by organisers. No data is written to NFC tags and no personal information is transmitted via NFC.</p>

<h3>Device and Usage Data</h3>
<p>We do not currently collect analytics or crash reports beyond what is inherent in Firebase services (e.g. Firebase Authentication uses standard Google infrastructure). No third-party analytics SDKs are installed in the app.</p>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<ul>
  <li>To record and display your activity history to you</li>
  <li>To calculate and display event results to participants and organisers</li>
  <li>To enable the TrailPass social encounter feature (opt-in only)</li>
  <li>To process event registration payments</li>
  <li>To maintain your account and authenticate you securely</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Sharing</h2>
<p>We do not sell your personal data. Data is shared only in the following circumstances:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Event organisers</strong> — can see participant GPS trails and punch records for events they organise</li>
  <li><strong>Friends</strong> — if you add someone as a friend, they can see your activity summaries</li>
  <li><strong>Service providers</strong> — Google Firebase (authentication, database, storage) and Stripe (payments) process data on our behalf under their respective privacy policies</li>
  <li><strong>Legal requirements</strong> — if required by law or to protect the rights and safety of users</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
<p>Your account data is retained for as long as your account is active. You may delete your account and all associated data by contacting us (see Section 7). Locally cached map tiles are stored on-device and cleared when you use the "Clear tile cache" option in Settings.</p>

<h2>5. Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>game:out is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will delete it.</p>

<h2>6. Security</h2>
<p>We use industry-standard measures including TLS in transit and Firebase Security Rules to protect your data. No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure; we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

<h2>7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Access and export</strong> — you can view all your activity data within the app</li>
  <li><strong>Deletion</strong> — contact us to delete your account and all data</li>
  <li><strong>TrailPass opt-out</strong> — disable BLE scanning at any time in Settings → TrailPass</li>
  <li><strong>Location</strong> — revoke location permission via your device OS settings (the app will not be able to record activities)</li>
</ul>

<h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top will reflect any changes. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

<h2>9. Contact</h2>
<p>Questions or requests about your data: <a href="mailto:privacy@gameout.app">privacy@gameout.app</a></p>

